<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="48" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,291,641]" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,328,352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is derived from lithos, which is Greek for stone, and the generic name 
<taxonomicName authority="Eschoscholtz, 1818" authorityName="Eschoscholtz" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Anthypna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1244,1352,328,352]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">Anthypna</emphasis>
Eschoscholtz, 
<number box="[244,303,364,388]" pageId="1" pageNumber="48" value="1818.0">1818</number>
</taxonomicName>
. Gender: feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,291,641]" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,399,424]" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Winged. Body elongate, length about 
<quantity box="[755,837,399,423]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
. Labrum large, approximately twice as wide as long, somewhat bilobed, sinuate in the middle. Clypeus with truncate, straight apical margin. Scutellum exposed, Ushaped. Elytra elongate, without striae, dehiscent at apex. Elytral lateral margin arcuate. Pygidium visible beyond elytra. Mesocoxae moderately separated. Mesofemur narrow. Protibia with three large denticles on the outer margin. Protarsus longer than protibia, non-lamellate medially. Metatibia with single, transverse carina on the outer margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,291,641]" box="[197,1247,615,641]" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">
